// 27.785 — 🟣 DOH-medical online pricing — sister-port of glw v36.485 (Doug 2026-05-17 build-it). Customer-site rendering for the inv-app v406.525 schema ship. When a SKU is flagged `is_doh_compliant` in the staff app: every product card on `/menu-preview` now carries a small purple 🟣 DOH badge top-left of the image (informational for all customers — these are the extra-tested SKUs that pass the WA DOH tier on top of the WSLCB safety panel). When the signed-in customer is ALSO DOH-card-verified (`customers.doh_verified_at` non-null per inv-app migration 0262, staff sets via the new DohVerifyPanel on /admin/customers/[id]): the card swaps the rec/online-discount price block for a **medical no-tax** price tier — rec price strikethrough above + purple medical-no-tax headline + 🟣 "Medical · no tax" sub-label. Math: shelf prices are tax-inclusive, so medical price = `effective_online_price / (1 + EXCISE_RATE + SALES_TAX_RATE)`. **Seattle defaults** (the wedge vs. glw's Wen defaults): 37% excise + 10.55% sales = divisor 1.4755 → ~32.2% off the post-online-discount price (BOTH tax tiers stripped per RCW 82.08.9998 + RCW 69.50.535(6)(a) since the DOH-card path is the full-exemption tier, NOT the recommending-physician path which only strips sales tax). Env-overridable via `NEXT_PUBLIC_EXCISE_RATE` + `NEXT_PUBLIC_SALES_TAX_RATE`. Non-DOH-verified customers + non-DOH-compliant products: zero change to current rendering. **New SSoT:** `lib/medical-pricing.ts` with pure `medicalNoTaxPrice(shelfPrice)` helper. **New customer-state lookup:** `getMedicalStatusByClerkId(clerkUserId)` in `lib/portal.ts` returns `{ isMedical, dohVerifiedAt }` — same Clerk-user → portal_users → customers email-join the existing `getLoyaltyByClerkId` uses. **One caller wired:** `/menu-preview` page-root resolves dohVerified once (server-side, after Clerk auth resolves) and passes it down through OrderMenu's new `dohVerified?: boolean` prop. (Sister glw also wires `/order` — scc's `/order` is just a `redirect("/menu")` so no equivalent.) **What this does NOT yet do** (Phase 2 of `PLAN_DOH_MEDICAL_TAX_SEPARATION_2026_05_11.md`): the POS register still charges full tax at the till; tax-exempt reconciliation remains off-system at LIQ-1295 filing time. The customer-site display is informational — it tells the patient what they SHOULD ring up at, and signals to staff at pickup that this is a DOH-exempt ticket. typecheck queued.
