// 21.805 — 🪝 React Rules-of-Hooks refactor — `components/CartResumeBanner.tsx`. Found via parallel-agent escalation (Explore audit of glw components, MEDIUM severity). Pre-fix: 5 hooks called AFTER an early `if (!PUBLIC_ORDER_ROUTE_LIVE) return null` guard, each marked `// eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/rules-of-hooks`. Worked while the flag was a compile-time constant (zero hooks called per render = consistent) BUT would silently break the moment the flag becomes dynamic state/prop — React would see different hook counts on different renders → "Rendered fewer hooks than expected" production crash. Refactor: moved all hooks (usePathname + useState×2 + useEffect×3) above the guard, then check `!PUBLIC_ORDER_ROUTE_LIVE`. Dropped 8 eslint-disable comments. Behavior unchanged while flag is false; future-proof when flag flips. Sister glw v30.005. tsc + 368/368 clean. Pre-commit Explore review CLEAN.
// 21.705 — 🛡️ proxy.ts CANONICAL_HOST allow-list (site-wide-outage prevention). Found via memory pin `feedback_env_defense_allow_list_not_deny_list` after the v21.605 email-defense sweep — the middleware reads `NEXT_PUBLIC_CANONICAL_HOST` env with ZERO defense (no .vercel.app reject, no hostname-allow-list). If env drifted to a typo (e.g. `app.seattlecannabis.co`), EVERY non-canonical request would 308-redirect to that broken host = SITE-WIDE OUTAGE. Higher-impact than the email-defense sites because the redirect target affects every page load, not just outbound CTAs. Fix: ALLOWED_CANONICAL_HOSTS Set + IIFE-validated CANONICAL_HOST. Empty/undefined env → fallback. Non-allowed value → fallback. Only allowed value flows through. 2-step migration intentional safety (add to allow-list code FIRST, then flip env). Existing ALWAYS_CANONICAL_HOSTS preserved — orthogonal purpose (source hosts not redirected vs destination hosts env can override to). Pre-commit Explore review confirmed zero regression (fallback matches the prior `|| "www..."` value exactly + .env.example never set this var). Sister glw v29.905. tsc + 368/368 clean.
