// 21.405 — 🚨 BUG FIX + 3 NEW TESTS — Resend silent-failure defense. Sister of inv v305.205 fix (project_resend_silent_failure_2026_05_08.md). Pre-fix `lib/email.ts:104` read `r.data?.id` without first checking `r.error`. Resend v4 returns a discriminated union `{ data, error: null } | { data: null, error: ErrorResponse }` — does NOT throw on rejection. When Resend rejected (unverified domain, rate-limit, invalid recipient), the code fell through to `"Resend returned no message id"` losing the diagnostic info. Doug 2026-05-08/09 inv incident showed this silent-failure class costs hours to diagnose ("emails not arriving despite admin UI showing 'sent'"). Now: branch on `r.error` BEFORE returning success, surface `error.name` (typed code key like "validation_error" — no PII) but NEVER `error.message` (may echo recipient address). Plus 3 fs.readFileSync tests in email-templates.test.ts to lock the defense: (a) r.error checked before return, (b) console.error never references error.message (PII risk), (c) catch block uses e.name (PII strip pattern). Sister glw v29.605. 364/364 full suite green + tsc clean.
