// 19.905 — 🚨 HIGH-PRIORITY WSLCB COMPLIANCE — llms-full.txt residual efficacy claim caught by live-probe (sister glw v28.405). The arc-guard `check-efficacy-claims.mjs` regex missed the sentence shape "Indica strains are traditionally associated with relaxing, body-heavy effects. Sativas tend toward more energizing, uplifting effects." — patterns: "associated with relaxing" + "tend toward more energizing/uplifting". Earlier regex only caught "tends toward sedating/uplifting/calming/relaxing" without "more" qualifier + didn't catch "associated with" pattern. Fixes: (1) Rewrote the indica/sativa Q&A in llms-full.txt to preference framing: "Quick rule of thumb: indica leans body-heavy, sativa leans head-forward, hybrid is a blend of both. It's a simplification — terpene profile shapes how a strain lands more than the indica/sativa label." Matches /faq v17.505 + /learn v17.305 canonical voice. (2) Also caught nearby Q "Budtenders love helping first-time customers... consume safely" — same v17.505 doctrine swap to "first-time customers are the favorite kind... start-low guidance". (3) EXTENDED arc-guard regex to catch both new shapes: `tends? toward (more)? (...)` and `associated with (relaxing|energizing|uplifting|...)`. Future-prevention for the broader sentence-shape class. AI engines (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google AI-Overview) crawl /llms-full.txt directly — this was directly feeding therapeutic-claim language to AI overviews. Sister glw v28.405.
// 19.805 — 🌐 SEO — JSON-LD schema completeness on /terms-of-use + /health-data-policy. Live-probe audit revealed 2 pages emitting ONLY root-layout schema (Organization + WebSite + LocalBusiness) — no page-specific WebPage or BreadcrumbList. Added WebPage schema with mainEntity → LocalBusiness @id linkage + BreadcrumbList for both pages. Now both have 5 JSON-LD blocks matching the /about + /menu + /faq pattern. AI engines (Anthropic AI-Overview, OpenAI, Google) recognize these as authoritative store-authored pages — load-bearing for HB 1155 in particular (the /health-data-policy page IS the legal disclosure surface; should be entity-linked). Sister glw v28.305. Caught by fresh "audit-the-newest-code" lane: probed each page's JSON-LD blocks via curl + Python parse to verify schema validity + completeness. Earlier audits assumed schema was present; live-probe revealed which pages were emitting zero page-level structured data.
// 19.705 — ⚡ PERF — InstallAppBanner idle-gate (vercel:performance-optimizer P3 catch). Pre-fix: banner ran ALL setup synchronously on first paint of every route (root-layout-mounted) — platform detect via UA sniffing, localStorage reads, beforeinstallprompt subscription, standalone-launch tracking POST. Even though `if (!visible) return null` early-returned the render, the useEffect ran. Post-fix: added `ready` state initialized false, flipped true via `requestIdleCallback` (with `setTimeout(1500)` fallback for browsers without it). The platform-detect useEffect now gates on `[ready]` — runs only AFTER browser idle. ServiceWorkerRegister already had this pattern since earlier work. Per perf agent estimate: INP -10-30ms on first-paint interactions, TBT -50-100ms Lighthouse. Sister glw v28.205.
// 19.605 — ⚡ PERF — HeroBackground content-visibility:auto (vercel:performance-optimizer P3 catch). The 5-layer animated hero bg (3 drifting pools + 2 corner blobs + 3 sparse particles) on 18-40s CSS keyframes. Previously only gated by prefers-reduced-motion; on a mobile homepage with 8+ sections, hero is offscreen 90% of scroll but still compositing (browser auto-throttle is for hidden tabs, not just-scrolled-past). Added `[content-visibility:auto]` Tailwind arbitrary-value class on the `.hero-bg` wrapper. Browsers skip rendering the layer entirely when scrolled out of viewport. Safe: HeroBackground is absolute inset-0 over the hero section; section height doesn't depend on this layer's render so no CLS. Expected impact: low-end mobile scroll FPS +5-10 per perf agent (not a CWV-dashboard win, but a "feels smoother" win on $200 Androids). Scc-only — glw doesn't have HeroBackground.
// 19.505 — ⚡ PERF — /menu CLS defense: min-h-[60vh] on iHJ Boost #app mount div. Continuing the deferred-perf-finding backlog from earlier parallel-agent audit. Pre-fix: empty `<div id="app" />` had zero reserved height, so when Boost JS hydrated and injected the product grid (400-900px depending on viewport + product count), MenuActiveDealsStrip + AppOnlyDealsFilter + MenuFallback + MenuLocalStrip all shifted down. Post-fix: min-h-[60vh] reserves ~500px mobile / ~700px desktop pre-paint. Net CLS reduction: ~0.05-0.10 on first /menu paint per perf agent P2 estimate. The 60vh choice: viewport-aware (scales with screen), close enough to typical Boost render that residual shift is minimal, defensive without aggressive dead-space on small screens. Sister glw v28.105.
// 19.405 — ⚡ PERF — VendorAdSlot fetchPriority + explicit width/height (vercel:performance-optimizer P2 catch). When VendorAdSlot is loading="eager" (homepage_top usage in app/page.tsx), the eager attribute alone doesn't signal browser priority for LCP — the image races the hero h1 unprioritized. Added fetchPriority="high" when loading is eager + explicit width="280" height="210" attributes so the slot reserves layout space pre-paint. Aspect-ratio classes (aspect-[4/3] + sm:min-h-[160px]) already mitigate CLS but explicit dimensions are HTML-spec-correct + redundancy is defensive. Expected impact when slot populated: LCP -200-500ms, CLS -0.02-0.05 (per perf agent). No-op when slot is empty (component returns null). Sister glw v28.005.
// 19.305 — 🛡️ 6TH ARC-GUARD — check-apologize-pattern.mjs locks the brand-voice doc "never apologize for things that aren't our fault" rule at baseline 0. Build-gates 28→29 cross-stack. Catches 4 corporate-apology patterns: "we apologize" / "We're sorry," / "sorry for the" / "sorry about that". Recurred 2 times this session pre-guard (v18.105 /terms-of-use disclaimer apology stripped + v18.705 MenuFallback iHJ-failure apology reframed). Both stores currently pass 0 — guard locks baseline against future regression. Doctrine rationale: apology = concession of fault, dilutes legal posture on disclaimer copy AND signals copywriter-not-shopkeeper voice on customer-facing surfaces. Sister glw v27.905. 6 doctrinal arc-guards now active cross-stack covering all recurring brand-voice + compliance + WSLCB doctrines from this 48-ship session.
// 19.205 — 🛡️ 5TH ARC-GUARD — check-template-warmth.mjs + 3 file fixes. Build-gates 27→28 cross-stack. Catches corporate-template warmth softeners: "give us a call/ring", "drop us a line", "reach out to us". First run caught 3 fixes on scc (after the 3 customer-facing fixes I'd just shipped pre-guard): (1) /order/confirmation/[id]:285 "Just give us a call — we'll hold it." → "Call us — we'll hold it." (2) /community:102 "drop us a line at" → "email us at". (3) /order-confirmation-email.ts:259 + /lib/posts.ts:114 — 2 more "give us a call" residuals caught after first 3 fixes. All swapped to direct verbs. Doctrine: real shop voice is direct, not template-warmth. "Give us a call" reads as a copywriter trying to sound friendly; "Call us" is what an actual budtender says. Sister glw v27.805 ports same guard + 3 fixes (careers + 2 lib hits).
