// 19.005 — ⚡ SYSTEMIC OG CACHE-CONTROL — 6 scc static OG routes (per-store parity sweep caught systemic gap past saturation). Triggered by previous-round audit-miss recovery (v18.905 HB 1155 sister-port miss). Per-store-parity-grep across all static OG files found 6 scc routes serving stale social previews because Vercel defaults to short TTL without explicit s-maxage. The dynamic [slug]/[id]/[cohort] OG routes had headers since v8.205 cohort fix, the static parents did not. Files patched: app/opengraph-image.tsx (homepage — highest-share surface), /press, /about, /community, /find-your-strain, /visit. All now have 24h max-age + 7d stale-while-revalidate matching the dynamic-route pattern + the /heroes parent fix v18.705. Sister glw v27.605 ports same fix to 10 glw static OG routes. Net: 16 cross-stack OG files now consistent. Production-impact: social shares from these surfaces (Facebook/Twitter/LinkedIn/Discord previews) no longer serve stale graphics on repeat-visits or after copy updates propagate.
// 18.905 — 🚨 LEGAL/POLICY — HB 1155 hardening cross-port from glw v26.805. Earlier session audit incorrectly flagged scc as "missing /health-data-policy sister page" — it DOES exist (app/health-data-policy/page.tsx, 361 lines), I missed it. But the 3 HB 1155 fixes I applied to glw v26.805 had NEVER been ported to scc — same drift across the sister file. Cross-port: (1) NEVER_SOLD list "We do not sell your consumer health data to anyone, ever." → "We do not sell your consumer health data." Drops "to anyone, ever" forever-promise (hard to defend if business is sold per Doug 2026-05-02 ownership directive + successor-in-interest provisions). Unqualified version matches HB 1155 statutory language. (2) Right-to-withdraw line "We honor withdrawals as fast as we can; in practice, within five business days." → "We honor withdrawals within five business days." Strips the "as fast as we can" hedge. (3) HOW_TO_REQUEST subject-line dark-pattern fix — added parenthetical "(the subject line just helps us route faster — requests without it are still honored)". Under HB 1155 (RCW 19.373) you can't condition rights-exercise on a specific format — that would be a non-compliant dark pattern. Both stores' /health-data-policy pages are now at consistent HB 1155 hardening. The "scc has no sister" note in earlier Doug-decision list was wrong + retracted.
// 18.805 — 📝 Signed-in customer-portal copy sweep — 5 catches across /account/orders + /account/profile + ProfileForm (communications-expert parallel-agent escalation round 2 — past saturation lane producing real signal). These are intimate post-auth moments where tone slips land harder than on public pages. (1) /account/orders.tsx substitution-summary line "🔄 Substitution{s} made by staff" → "🔄 We swapped {one|a couple} for you · same category, fresh stock". This is the MOST emotionally-charged signed-in beat (customer paid for X and got Y) — passive audit-log voice swapped to active "we" with rationale-in-line. (2) /account/orders.tsx empty-state "Your pickup order history will appear here" → "Your pickup history will appear here." (matches brand-voice doc canonical version line 207; strips redundancy with adjacent "No orders yet" headline + ends with period). (3) /account/profile/page.tsx breadcrumb "My Account" → "Account" (brand-voice doc table customer = "You" not "My"). (4) /account/profile/page.tsx subhead "Email is managed by your sign-in provider." → "Your email comes from however you signed in — change it there." Strips "sign-in provider" dev-speak (engineer's name for Clerk) → concrete customer-facing instruction. (5) ProfileForm.tsx Heroes dropdown — "None captured" (CRM database-status talk) → "— Not one of these —" (neutral default option), plus paired body line "Bring your credential to verify at the counter — this just lets us know to expect it" → "Bring your service ID and we'll apply it at the counter — this just tells us to expect it" ("credential" = HR vocab → brand-voice canonical "service ID"; "verify" sounds adversarial → "apply" sounds like staff serving). Sister glw v27.505 same-turn cross-port (identical patterns).
// 18.705 — 📝 /menu chrome + /heroes OG Cache-Control (3 catches; parallel-agent escalation past saturation per memory pin `feedback_parallel_agent_escalation_past_round_30`). Solo grinding had declared saturation; communications-expert agent audited /menu chrome — surface that's HIGHEST-conversion + I'd never fully audited because the iHJ embed isn't ours. Caught 2 chrome-specific issues. Explorer agent caught a CRITICAL OG Cache-Control miss. (1) MenuFallback.tsx (the iHJ-failure error state) — pre-fix H2 "Our live menu is taking a moment to load." apologizes for a vendor (iHJ) failure that's not ours. Per brand-voice "never apologize for things that aren't our fault" rule. Post-fix: "Menu's slow today — here's how to order while it loads." Leads with the action lane instead of the apology. (2) MenuFallback.tsx body pre-fix: "...while we get the embedded menu back, or give us a call — we have everything ready..." Two issues: "embedded menu" is back-office register-speak ("embedded" is what WE call it, customer says "the menu"), AND "while we get the [it] back" implies we can fix iHJ on the spot (we can't — third-party). Post-fix: "Order on iHeartJane while it loads, or call us — we've got everything ready..." Drops back-office speak + the false-implication. (3) /heroes/opengraph-image.tsx CRITICAL — parent route missing Cache-Control headers that the /heroes/[cohort] OG had since v8.205. Vercel defaults to short TTL without explicit s-maxage so social shares of /heroes were serving stale previews to repeat viewers (high-impact since /heroes is the highest-traffic acquisition CTA). Post-fix: same 24h max-age + 7d swr headers as the cohort variant. Sister glw v27.405 same-turn — same 2 MenuFallback fixes + same /heroes OG Cache-Control + glw-specific /our-story OG fixes (Doug 2026-05-07 staff-name removal leaked through to OG image; "Doug · Kat · Charity · Wes · Shailey · Jess" baked into the rendered graphic → swapped to "Center Road · Wenatchee" non-PII framing + same Cache-Control headers added). Parallel-agent escalation lifted real saturation: 4 ship-worthy catches in 5 minutes after solo grinding declared no fresh signal.
// 18.605 — 📝 "Please" hedge cleanup — 3 form-validation error strings. Pre-fix: "Please enter a valid email address.", "Please enter at least a 10-digit phone number.", "Please enter a valid email." Per brand-voice doc "What we never do" rule + v4.565 prior /apply form pattern, customer-facing error messages drop the "Please" hedge — direct instruction reads firmer + matches shop voice. Post-fix: "Enter a valid email address.", "Enter a 10-digit phone number.", "Enter a valid email." Sites fixed: app/vendor-access/VendorAccessForm.tsx, app/rewards/login/LoginForm.tsx, app/find-your-strain/StrainFinderClient.tsx. Sister glw v27.305 same-turn cross-port (2 sister hits — glw doesn't have a /rewards/login form, that's scc-only). Caught by ad-hoc "Please" grep past arc-guard saturation. Three doctrinal guards in place still don't catch the "Please" hedge class — could be a 4th guard in a future round, but this class has lower recurrence than the 3 already-built.
// 18.505 — 🛡️ 2 ARC-GUARDS + 2 catches — check-efficacy-claims.mjs + check-loyalty-math-drift.mjs (build-gates 24→26 cross-stack). Memory-pin → arc-guard mining lane continues. (1) check-efficacy-claims.mjs enforces WAC 314-55-155 doctrine — flags causation framing ("tends toward sedating", "takes the edge off", "calmer cannabinoid"), therapeutic verb + condition pairings ("helps with anxiety", "good for sleep", "relieves pain"), pharmacological descriptors ("anxiolytic", "anti-inflammatory"), and the Senior→Wisdom rename residual class. Passes 0 on both stores after the v17.305 + v17.505 + v17.605 + v18.305 sweeps. Exempts brand-page _brands/* (3rd-party marketing voice) + scripts/ + version.ts. (2) check-loyalty-math-drift.mjs enforces Doug 2026-05-07 canonical math — flags "1 point per $1" + "100 points = $1" + "$1 off per 100 points" patterns. First run caught 2 residuals in app/llms-full.txt (AI-engine feed) that the welcome-email + /faq + /deals sweeps missed — both fixed same-turn with sliding-ladder canonical framing. Guard intentionally exempts lib/portal.ts + components/LoyaltyCard.tsx as known implementation divergence (POINTS_PER_DOLLAR=100 deployed math, Doug-decision pending POS-register parity verification). Sister glw v27.205 ports both guards + the 2 llms-full.txt fixes. Build-gates 26/26 cross-stack now.
// 18.405 — 🛡️ ARC-GUARD + 13 residual ownership-claim catches — memory-pin → arc-guard recipe past compliance-lens saturation. Built scripts/check-brand-voice-locally-owned.mjs to enforce Doug 2026-05-02 directive (NO "locally owned" framing) cross-stack. Guard catches all variants: "locally owned" / "Locally Owned" / "locally-owned" / "Locally-Owned" / "independently owned" / possessive-superlative-shop patterns like "Wenatchee's favorite shop". Wired into pre-push (24/24 gates). First run on scc immediately caught 13 residuals the ad-hoc grep sessions missed — regex case-and-dash-insensitive: (1) app/about/opengraph-image.tsx:105 "Locally owned." (social-share image). (2-8) app/about/page.tsx — 7 hits across metadata description + keywords + OG title/description + AboutPage schema description + body H2 + value-prop card title. Card title "Locally Owned" → "Same Crew Since 2010". Body "Seattle Cannabis Co. is a locally owned, independent cannabis dispensary" → "Seattle Cannabis Co. is an independent cannabis dispensary... Same crew, same care." Plus efficacy-claim residual on line 107 "seeking relief, relaxation, creativity" → "body-heavy evening, daytime session, creative moment" (sister of /learn v17.305 sweep). (9) app/find-your-strain/page.tsx:153 "Locally-owned since 2010" → "Same crew since 2010". (10-12) app/llms.txt/route.ts:56 + 66 — 3 hits in AI-engine feed Q&A. (13) app/visit/page.tsx:199 "Locally owned since 2010" → "Same crew since 2010", plus stale defensive comment ("Locally-owned IS the framing here") rewritten to reference the arc-guard. The session's KEY LEARNING: defensive code comments justifying brand-voice exemptions ARE the trap (3rd recurrence — scc home v17.805, scc /visit v18.405, both caught by same pattern). Arc-guard is the only systemic fix. Sister glw v27.105 ports the guard + pre-push wiring (glw passes guard with 0 residuals).
// 18.305 — 🚨 HIGH-PRIORITY WSLCB COMPLIANCE — quiz-nurture-email.ts customer-direct efficacy-claim fix. strainPhrase() helper returned customer-visible labels with predictable-effect attribution: sativa "(uplifting, daytime)" + indica "(relaxing, nighttime)". Same pattern as the /faq + /learn + /blog efficacy-claim sweeps — predictable-effect-attribution = WAC 314-55-155 tripwire. These strings flowed into the D+0 "Your strain match is in" email + the D+2 follow-ups + the D+5 nudge series (3+ touchpoints per quiz taker). Post-fix: sativa "(head-forward, daytime-leaning)" + indica "(body-heavy, evening-leaning)" + hybrid "(in-between)". Strips the therapeutic verbs ("uplifting", "relaxing") while preserving the descriptive shorthand. Sister glw v27.005 same-turn cross-port.
// 18.205 — 🚨 LOYALTY MATH DRIFT — welcome-email.ts customer-direct fix (extends /faq v17.505 + /deals v17.405 cross-stack sweep). Pre-fix: every new customer who signed up got a welcome email saying "Earn 1 point per $1 spent in store. Redeem 100 points = $1 off your next visit." Both numbers are wrong per docs/brand-voice.md canonical loyalty math: (a) earn rate is 0.5pt/$1 (opted-in to SMS or email) or 0.25pt/$1 (neither) — NOT 1pt/$1; (b) redemption ladder is 50pt→5%, 100pt→10%, 200pt→20%, 250pt→25%, 300pt→30% (<$75), 400pt→30% ($75+) — NOT linear $1/100pt. Post-fix HTML + plain-text versions: "Every visit earns points (more if you're opted in to SMS or email). Points redeem on a sliding ladder — 50pt for 5% off, 100pt for 10%, on up to 30% off at 300-400pt." Accurate, concise, matches the redemption ladder customers see at the counter. Welcome email is the FIRST DIRECT TOUCH for every signup → wrong-math sets wrong-expectation at scale. Higher-priority than the public-page versions (which were already fixed in v17.405 + v17.505) because the email is opened in the inbox without web context. Sister glw v26.905 same-turn cross-port.
// 18.105 — 📝 /terms-of-use — never-apologize-on-disclaimers fix (1 catch). Line 143-147: pre-fix "We try to keep the site fresh and we apologize for any frustration when stock or price differs. The price at the register controls the transaction." Apology on a clause that's already a disclaimer concedes fault on something explicitly framed as not-warranted. Post-fix: "The price and stock at the register control the transaction." Drops the apology + "we try to keep the site fresh" softener; tightens the disclaimer's legal posture. Sister glw v26.805 same-turn cross-port. Never-apologize-on-disclaimers principle per brand-voice doc "What we never do" rule.
// 18.005 — 🚨 HIGH-PRIORITY WSLCB COMPLIANCE — Reviews.tsx customer-testimonial compliance + brand-voice (2 catches on scc + sister glw v26.705). Reviews.tsx renders fabricated customer testimonials on the homepage (line 1303 of app/page.tsx). Schema.org JSON-LD emission was already stripped (v13.7405 — Google "self-serving reviews" policy + FTC scrutiny) but the visual display still rendered them as if they were real customer voices. Found 2 ship-today issues in the testimonial text itself: (1) Senior-customer testimonial line 39 originally said "I'm a senior who started using cannabis for chronic pain. The staff have been patient, kind..." Putting "chronic pain" + "cannabis" in customer-attributed copy on a cannabis retailer site is a WSLCB therapeutic-claim tripwire whether or not the customer voice is real — it's still the SHOP publishing the claim. Stripped to "I started using cannabis later in life and was nervous to walk in. The staff have been patient, kind..." Preserves the warmth + age-respect + tinctures/dosing framing; removes the condition-attribution. (2) Line 46 customer review "Locally owned and you can feel it — disciplined, well-run, no nonsense" → "Independent shop, you can feel it — disciplined, well-run, no nonsense." Same ownership-claim risk as v17.805+v17.905 sweep. "Independent" is the anti-chain framing that's safe (it's about NOT being a chain/MSO, not making an ownership claim). NOTE for follow-up: the broader question of whether to keep ANY fabricated customer testimonials on a customer-facing page is a Doug-decision. The header comment already acknowledges these are "curated copy, not verified first-party reviews"; the path forward is real Google review pull via pull-gbp-reviews/route.ts in the inv app once approval lands. communications-expert recipe: not strictly an audit (caught by ad-hoc cross-stack grep + manual file read), but same compliance lens.
// 17.905 — 📝 RESIDUAL "locally owned" sweep — 5 MORE surfaces caught by cross-stack grep after v17.805 home-page fix. v17.805 caught the most visible drift; this ship closes the AI-crawler-facing + OG-image + order-flow + press surfaces that were hiding the same framing. (1) app/opengraph-image.tsx — "Locally owned · Open since 2010 · 8 AM–11 PM daily" → "16+ years in cannabis · Open since 2010 · 8 AM–11 PM daily". This renders into the social-share card image that Facebook/Twitter/LinkedIn previews show — high cross-platform reach. (2) app/llms.txt — Q&A "Is ${name} locally owned?" → "How long has ${name} been around?" with crew-and-care framing. Plus indica/sativa "traditionally relaxing/uplifting" → "traditionally body-heavy/head-forward" (efficacy-claim residual on the same AI-engine feed). (3) app/llms-full.txt — 2 spots "locally owned and locally operated" → tenure + crew framing. Both AI-engine feeds were emitting the stripped framing back into Anthropic/OpenAI/Google AI-overview crawls. (4) app/order/OrderMenu.tsx:1317 H2 "Locally owned since 2010." → "Same crew, same care since 2010." — high-conversion order-flow surface. (5) app/press/page.tsx — Owner row "Green Anne LLC · locally owned, independent" → "Green Anne LLC · 16+ years in Rainier Valley" + body paragraph "Locally owned, neighborhood-staffed" → "Neighborhood-staffed since 2018". Sister glw v26.605 same-turn cross-port for llms-full.txt. All 5 surfaces now consistent with v17.805 home-page + v17.105 careers + v25.505 press doctrine. The recurring lesson: defensive code comments justifying brand-voice exemptions ARE the trap.
