// 17.705 — 📝 /accessibility hedge-stripping sweep (communications-expert audit, 4 catches). Pattern: classic accessibility-template hedges replaced with the commitments the body of the page already backs up. (1) Hero subtitle "how we work to keep this site usable" → "how we keep" — pre-emptive excuse for gaps that the WCAG 2.1 AA + two-day fix SLA below contradicts. (2) Communication-accommodations card "We do not currently have an ASL interpreter on staff" → "No ASL interpreter on staff" — double-hedge ("currently" + "do not have") stripped, immediately pivots to what we DO offer (video-relay arranged ahead). (3) "We will work with you on what fits the visit" → "Tell us what you need and we'll set it up before you come in" — HR-template ("we'll see what we can do") replaced with action-named promise the customer can act on. (4) "We aim for WCAG 2.1 Level AA conformance" → "We build to WCAG 2.1 Level AA" — same risk-posture (still not claiming full conformance) but commits to the standard as the spec, not the aspiration. The 8 specific commitments below back this up. Sister glw v26.505 same-turn cross-port. communications-expert recipe 22-for-22.
