// 9.625 — 🛡️ DB-DoS defense — added per-IP rate limit (20/min) on `/api/rewards/verify-code`. Pre-fix: each call ran a DB SELECT on `loyalty_otp_codes` by phone (composite-indexed but still a DB hop) + sometimes UPDATE on `attempts`. With NO per-IP cap, an attacker could fire 1000 req/s from one IP → DB-load DoS, even though MAX_ATTEMPTS=5 per row makes brute-force infeasible. Adopted `createRateLimiter` (the v9.525 helper) at 20/min/IP — generous (legit users enter 1-3 attempts per OTP), tight enough to slow scripted DB load. Returns 429 + Retry-After:60. Different shape than `/api/rewards/request-code` (DB-backed COUNT-based 5/hr there — cheaper to persist for that volume; in-memory is right for verify's higher hot-path traffic). Caught by /loop iteration auditing rewards/* routes for missing per-IP defense. tsc clean.
// 9.525 — 🛡️ Cross-repo class fix — extracted `lib/rate-limit.ts` shared helper + adopted across 5 public-API routes that had unbounded-Map rate limiters (/api/quiz/capture, /api/push/subscribe, /api/push/unsubscribe, /api/track-install, /api/orders). Pre-fix: each route had its own private `Map<key,{count,resetAt}>` with NO pruning of expired entries → unbounded growth on long-lived Vercel Fluid Compute instances. These are public endpoints (cellular IPs rotate frequently) so a 24h instance lifetime could accumulate ~10K stale entries (~500KB) before falling out. Helper opportunistically prunes (1% probability per call, O(n) bounded amortised cost). Sister: `Inventory App/src/lib/rate-limit.ts` (v345.805 + v346.205 there, 17 routes) + glw v8.305 same wave. 3-repo class coverage now closed. Audit: `grep 'new Map<string, { count: number; resetAt: number }>' app lib | wc -l` returns 0. tsc clean.
// 9.345 — 🛡️ Security header — `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin` restored. The lone remaining 2026-05-01-removed header. Pre-fix the customer surface had NO Referrer-Policy → default browser behavior leaked full URL+query to external image hosts / analytics on every cross-origin request → /rewards?token=… / /quiz?session=… / any session-token-bearing query param could surface in third-party referer logs. Why safe vs iHJ Boost: Referrer-Policy controls OUTBOUND referer only; Boost's inbound trust-token redemption is Permissions-Policy gated (already in place). Already shipping on inv + GW + cannagent + glw (sister-shipped same day v8.125). Closes the cross-site drift caught by /loop saturation grind 2026-05-09 security-header audit. tsc + lint clean.
// 9.325 — 🔍 SEO fix — `/apply` canonical was incorrectly pointing at `/` (homepage). Pre-fix `<link rel="canonical">` on /apply rendered as `https://www.seattlecannabis.co` instead of `https://www.seattlecannabis.co/apply` because `app/apply/page.tsx` is a client component (`"use client"` for the multi-step form state) — Next 16 client components can't export `metadata`, so the page silently inherited the root layout's canonical (`/`). Google then treated /apply as a duplicate of homepage and refused to index it as a separate page — anyone Googling "Seattle Cannabis Co apply for job" would not find /apply in search results, real SEO loss for hiring funnel. Fix: added `app/apply/layout.tsx` (server component) with proper metadata + `alternates: { canonical: "/apply" }` + Open Graph + Twitter cards. Layout wraps the client-component page.tsx without forcing it to convert. Sister glw v8.105 same fix. /careers (sister page) was already correct because page.tsx is a server component there. Caught by /loop saturation grind 2026-05-09 canonical-URL audit. Audit recipe: `for path in /apply /careers /menu /near/rainier-valley /find-your-strain /deals; do canonical=$(curl -sL https://www.seattlecannabis.co$path | grep -oE '<link[^>]*rel="canonical"[^>]*' | head -1 | grep -oE 'href="[^"]+"'); echo "$path → $canonical"; done` — flag any canonical mismatch. tsc + lint clean.
// 9.305 — 🚨 SEO RECOVERY mirror of glw v8.085 — `/learn` was server-rendering ZERO content (CSR bailout). `await auth()` from Clerk + `await getCompletedSteps(userId)` triggered Next 16's BAILOUT_TO_CLIENT_SIDE_RENDERING — SSR returned only the loading.tsx spinner + a CSR-bailout marker. Google + AI crawlers saw zero h1, zero topic list, zero JSON-LD on /learn. **Fix**: extracted auth-dependent slice into `<UserStateAwareLearn>` async server component wrapped in `<Suspense fallback={<SignedOutLearn />}>`. Static hero + h1 + JSON-LD always ship in SSR shell. Added `.catch(() => new Set())` on `getCompletedSteps()` so DB blip doesn't blank the page. Page copied verbatim from glw v8.085 + s/emerald/indigo/g for scc accent. tsc clean.
// 9.285 — 📱 Public-site UX — iOS autofill + keyboard-hint sweep on customer + vendor forms. Sister of glw v8.065 (mirror commit). 3 files: (1) `app/vendor-access/VendorAccessForm.tsx` Field wrapper auto-derives `autoComplete` + `inputMode` from `type` (catches both Field calls + future ones). (2) `app/account/profile/ProfileForm.tsx` Name input gets `autoComplete=name`; Phone input gets `autoComplete=tel inputMode=tel`. (3) `app/menu/MenuSearch.tsx` adds the iOS code-entry trio (`autoCorrect=off autoCapitalize=off spellCheck=false`) + `enterKeyHint=search`. Same defense rationale: customers searching "GSC" or "OG" don't get auto-corrected. Sister of inv v322.405/v323.405 staff-side trio sweep. tsc clean.
// 9.265 — 🩹 Lint cleanup — 4 unescaped apostrophes on `/near` + `/near/[town]`. Same class as glw v8.045. Pre-fix `pnpm lint` failed; post-fix clean. tsc + lint clean.
// 9.245 — 🧹 /rewards page robots metadata consistency — added `follow: false` to match sister /rewards/* pages (login/verify/dashboard/redeem/history/balance all use `{ index: false, follow: false }`). Pre-fix /rewards had `{ index: false }` only — missing follow. Saves Google crawl budget: every sub-page Google follows from /rewards is itself noindex, so traversing them is pure waste. Pure metadata-block edit; tsc clean. Closes the rewards/* noindex consistency drift caught by /loop saturation grind robots-coverage audit.
// 9.225 — 🔁 Redirect-chain flatten — `/book` + `/book-now` were chaining 308 → /order → 307 /menu (3 hops). Now → /menu direct (single hop). Sister glw v8.025. tsc clean.
// 9.205 — 🔍 /brands/[slug] soft-404 mitigation — sister glw v8.005. generateMetadata now returns `robots: { index: false, follow: false }` on brand-not-found instead of empty `{}`. Prevents Google from indexing the ISR-cached not-found.tsx body served at HTTP 200. Brands can't use dynamicParams=false (active list is ISR-dynamic); noindex is the right defense for this shape. tsc clean.
// 9.185 — 🔍 /near/[town] soft-404 fix — added `export const dynamicParams = false`. Sister glw v7.985. Pre-fix /near/seattle + /near/wenatchee returned HTTP 200 with "Not found" content (soft-404, Google penalty class). Now any slug not in NEAR_TOWNS returns proper HTTP 404. tsc clean.
// 9.165 — ♿ /apply Suspense skeleton now ships an h1 — sister of glw v7.965. Pre-fix: ApplyPage wraps ApplyForm in `<Suspense fallback={<ApplyFormSkeleton/>}>` (Next 16 requires this for client-side useSearchParams). Skeleton had no h1 — initial SSR HTML had zero h1 tags. Crawlers + Lighthouse + screen-readers saw an h1-less page on first paint; h1 only appeared post-hydration. Now skeleton carries the same hero block as the form. tsc clean.
// 9.145 — 🔁 Legacy redirect mirror — 4 e-commerce-platform URL patterns added: `/cart` `/buy` `/pickup` `/preroll`. Pre-fix all 4 returned 404. Universal Shopify/WooCommerce legacy aliases + customer-intent URLs from loyalty/POS platforms + the singular sister of /pre-rolls. All 308 → /menu. Sister glw v7.945. Verified each was pre-fix 404 via curl. tsc clean.
// 9.125 — 🌲 Brand-page copy fix sister of v9.105 — `app/brands/[slug]/_brands/2k-gardens.tsx` had two more Wen→Sea port-over errors. Subtitle "120 Miles East" + body "Quincy to Wenatchee is two hours down US-2" (line 103-104) made geographic sense on glw but Sea customers reading "...to Wenatchee" wonder why this brand page is talking about Wenatchee. Sister fix in the closing paragraph (line 215-216): "Quincy is two hours down the road from Wenatchee, both ends of the same agricultural corridor". Both rewritten to Sea-relative geography: "150 Miles East" + "Quincy to Seattle is about three hours down I-90" + "Quincy is about three hours east of Seattle on I-90, a direct cross-state delivery". Quincy-to-Seattle distance verified: ~145mi on I-90, ~3hrs. Sister of v9.105 avitas same-class fix. Sweep recipe `grep -rnE "Sunnyslope|Wenatchee" app/ components/ lib/ --include="*.tsx"` flagged this. tsc clean.
// 9.105 — 🌲 Brand-page copy fix — `app/brands/[slug]/_brands/avitas.tsx:205` was a Wen→Sea port-over error: the body said "Mt. Hood, Three Sisters, the kind of view you actually get in Wenatchee's back yard". Wenatchee is on the OTHER side of the Cascades from Seattle (~150mi east) — the line reads as out-of-place to Sea customers + those mountains aren't actually in either store's "back yard" (Mt. Hood + Three Sisters are Oregon Cascades). Replaced with "the kind of view that holds across western Washington — reads honest because the cultivation is local (Arlington, an hour up I-5 from us)" which is geographically accurate (Avitas is in Arlington WA per glw L92 same file). Brand-voice is project-specific IP per operating-principle — Sea pages should read Seattle-local, not Wen-local. Found by /loop sister-fix sweep grep `Wenatchee|Sunnyslope|Green Life|greenlifecannabis` across scc components. tsc clean.
// 9.085 — 🩹 Customer-facing FAQ — Seattle local sales tax updated `~10.25%` → `~10.55%` per WA DOR AddressRates verification 2026-05-08 (King County 98118). Same rate that lib/tax.ts comment block was corrected to call out earlier (the under-collection / back-tax reconciliation Doug-action). Pre-fix customers reading the home-page FAQ saw "10.25%" but actual receipts show 10.55% — mismatch creates customer-trust issues + arguably mis-discloses pricing under WAC 314-55-155 transparency expectations. Found by /loop sister-fix sweep grep `0\\.0855|0\\.088|0\\.1055|10\\.25|10\\.55` across customer-facing components after the v9.045 metadata-cascade fix on /menu. Same wave as v316.805 launch-readiness row + v319.205 /api/health diagnostic. Single-string edit, no behavior change. tsc clean.
// 9.065 — 🔒 Privacy two-layer defense closure on `/rewards/balance`. This page accepts a `?phone=<digits>` querystring + renders the customer's first name + last initial + loyalty_points + last_visit_at. Pre-fix it had ZERO metadata block — protected only by robots.txt's `Disallow: /rewards` prefix. Sister pages (login/verify/dashboard/redeem/history) all emit page-level `robots: { index: false }`. /balance was the V0 query-string fallback that survived only as a smoke-test fallback during the cutover testing window (slated for deletion post-OTP-verification per file header). Until deletion, it gets the same two-layer defense as siblings — added `metadata.robots = { index: false, follow: false }`. Closes the screenshot/social-leak vector where a phone-in-querystring URL could land in SERP via index-despite-disallow. Single metadata export added; tsc clean. Audit recipe (sister of glw v7.925 /alumni layout fix): `for f in $(find app -name page.tsx); do has_meta=$(grep -c "robots:" $f); is_in_disallow=$(grep -F "$(dirname $f | sed s|^app||)" public/robots.txt 2>/dev/null | grep -c Disallow); ... `.
// 9.045 — 🥼 OG image on /menu — Next 16 metadata cascade quirk: page-level `openGraph: {...}` fully REPLACES parent's auto-injected images. Pre-fix `/menu` share previews on Slack/iMessage/Facebook rendered imageless because the page's openGraph override didn't include `images:`. glw side wasn't affected — it has `app/menu/opengraph-image.tsx` (per-route image) which Next auto-detects + injects despite the override. scc never grew that file, so reference the root `/opengraph-image` directly. Single `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` line addition. Sister of v8.745 fix on /order /careers /heroes/[cohort] /blog/[slug] (same wave that already swept the other affected pages). Audit recipe: `for f in $(find app -name page.tsx); do og=$(grep -c openGraph: $f); img=$(awk "/openGraph:/,/^\\s*\\}/" $f | grep -c images:); [ $og -gt 0 ] && [ $img -eq 0 ] && echo $f; done`. tsc clean.
// 9.025 — 🛡️ Rate-limit on `/api/push/subscribe` POST — sister of v9.005 unsubscribe fix. Pre-fix anon-or-Clerk-OK POST ran INSERT into push_subscriptions on every call. `auth()` is optional so anonymous browsers reach the upsert. The endpoint upsert dedupes on endpoint URL but a script rotating random fake endpoints could balloon push_subscriptions size + cron-fanout cost. Now: 10/min/IP in-memory Map, identical pattern to /api/push/unsubscribe (v9.005) + /api/track-install + /api/quiz/capture. 429 + Retry-After: 60 on cap. Sister glw v7.905. tsc clean.
// 9.005 — 🛡️ Rate-limit on `/api/push/unsubscribe` POST — gap caught by audit recipe. Pre-fix anon POST ran DB DELETE against push_subscriptions on a 1024-char endpoint string with NO rate-limit. Scripted attacker with captured endpoint URLs could mass-unsubscribe + spam-call to bog DB. Now: 10/min/IP in-memory Map, identical pattern to /api/track-install + /api/quiz/capture. 429 + Retry-After: 60 on cap. Sister glw v7.885 same fix. tsc clean.
// 8.985 — 🔁 Cross-store mirror-parity legacy redirects — `/about/mission` + `/about/location` were 404'ing on Sea but already 308'd on Wen. Closes the asymmetry: these are common WP-era nested-about URL patterns that stale Google index entries + partner-directory listings point at; pre-fix Sea customers landed on a 404. Now Sea 308s `/about/mission` → /about + `/about/location` → /visit (matching Wen's map). Sister glw v7.865 (mirror direction: glw gets `/book` + `/book-now` → /order which Sea had but Wen didn't). Single-block addition each side; tsc clean.
// 8.965 — 🔗 PWA manifest shortcut URL fix — `app/manifest.ts` "Order for Pickup" shortcut was URL `/order` (which proxy.ts 307s to /menu — extra redirect hop on iOS PWA install long-press menu) AND violated the customer-CTA-points-to-menu-only operating principle. Same class as v8.905 JSON-LD OrderAction.target sibling fix; this is the manifest-side variant. PWA shortcut now → `/menu` directly. Sister glw v7.845. Single-char URL change; tsc clean.
// 8.945 — 📱 iOS PWA polish — explicit `metadata.icons.apple` declaration in `app/layout.tsx`. Next 16 doesn't auto-emit `<link rel="apple-touch-icon">` when the icon is served by a route handler (we use `app/apple-icon.png/route.tsx` for dynamic ImageResponse generation). Pre-fix: HTML `<head>` had `<meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-title" content="Seattle Cannabis">` but NO `apple-touch-icon` link — iOS Safari "Add to Home Screen" fell back to a generic globe icon. The route already serves 200 + 180×180 PNG; this metadata change just points iOS at it. Sister glw v7.825. Single-block addition; tsc clean.
// 8.925 — ⚡ Perf — `loading="lazy"` added on 2 below-fold `<img>` tags that were missing it: `app/page.tsx` 🆕 New-this-week product card (section #11 of 11 on the home page, deep below-fold) + `components/VendorAdSlot.tsx` (vendor ad slot). VendorAdSlot fix is conditional via new `loading` prop (default `"lazy"`) — pre-commit Explore review caught that `homepage_top` slot at app/page.tsx:176 renders BEFORE the hero (above-fold on desktop), so that one usage now passes `loading="eager"` explicitly. The other 3 VendorAdSlot usages (`homepage_under_hero`, `homepage_under_brands`, `cross_store_promo`) inherit the lazy default. Sister glw v7.805. Single-attribute add per file; tsc clean.
// 8.905 — 🔗 JSON-LD `OrderAction.target` in app/layout.tsx now uses absolute URL (`${STORE.website}${STORE.shopUrl}` → `https://www.seattlecannabis.co/menu`) instead of bare `/menu` (relative path). Schema.org `Action.target` expects URL or EntryPoint; bare relative paths are ambiguous to Google's structured-data parser without the page context — risk is the OrderAction rich-result button doesn't render in SERP, OR Google falls back to the page URL. Sister glw v7.785 also points target at /menu (was /order — pre-fix glw routed customers to a redirected path). Both sites now consistently surface `/menu` as the canonical order entry point per the customer-CTAs-only-go-to-menu rule. Single-line edit, no behavior change for human visitors (same redirect chain works); structured-data parsers see a valid absolute URL.
// 8.885 — 🛡️ PII-leak round 4 sister of glw v7.745 — `app/api/quiz/capture/route.ts` had two leaks the v8.865 wrapper-source fix didn't catch (this route doesn't go through `lib/email.ts`). Line 170 was the D+0 dispatch catch around `dispatchD0Welcome` (Resend errors echo recipient email + sender domain in `err.message`). Line 177 was the surrounding INSERT catch — Drizzle wraps Postgres errors and the message echoes the conflicting row data (`(email)=(alice@example.com)`). Both rewritten as `err=${err instanceof Error ? err.name : "unknown"}`. Cross-repo /loop sister-fix sweep — same-file pattern shipped on glw + this in the same wave. tsc clean.
// 8.865 — 🛡️ PII-leak hardening at the email-wrapper source: `lib/email.ts:105` was logging + returning the full Resend SDK error message (`e.message`), which can echo recipient addresses. All callers (welcome-email, quiz-nurture-email, order-confirmation-email, admin actions) propagate `result.error` to their own `console.error` template. **Fix at the source:** the wrapper now logs + returns `e.name` only — every caller inherits the tightened result.error string. Sister glw v7.725 same-file fix. tsc clean.
// 8.845 — 🔒 /order/confirmation/[id] now `robots: noindex` + Disallow in app/robots.ts. Privacy-sensitive per-order page. Two-layer defense. Sister glw v7.705. tsc clean.
// 8.825 — 🏷️ %-off overlay on /devmenu + /order product cards (Doug 2026-05-08: "put the % off overlay on top of the product that is on sale similar to iheartjane"). Replaces the bottom-right "On Sale" chip (was UX_AUDIT_2026_05_03 P1-4 — sat too close to +Add and caused mistaps) with a prominent top-left red %-off badge that shows the actual discount magnitude (`20% OFF` or `$5 OFF` from `deal.discountType + discountValue`). At thumbnail scale a corner badge converts harder than a footer chip — the iHeartJane Boost embed on /menu uses this exact pattern, so customers already recognize it. Strain chip auto-displaces to bottom-right when a deal is present so corners stay non-overlapping (top-left = %-off, top-right = New / cart-quantity, bottom-left = weight, bottom-right = strain). Single-component edit at `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx`. Refactor: `findDealForProduct(...)` lifted out of nested IIFE to outer map closure (was being called inline; now memoized once per row). Sister glw v7.685. tsc clean.
// 8.805 — 🗺️ /order REMOVED from sitemap — proxy.ts 307-redirects /order/* → /menu. Listing redirected URLs in sitemap wastes Google crawl budget. Sister glw v7.665. tsc clean.
// 8.785 — 🔗 LocalBusiness @id graph-consolidation on /near pages — pre-fix each /near/<area> declared a separate LocalBusiness entity. Google's Knowledge Graph would treat each as a chain branch. Now @id references canonical home-page entity and `mainEntityOfPage` carries the per-page binding. Net effect: Google sees ONE business with 24 area-served declarations instead of 24 phantom branches. Sister glw v7.645. tsc clean.
// 8.765 — 📰 Article rich-result eligibility — `/blog/[slug]` Article LD now includes `image` field. Pre-fix no `image` so Google can't promote to article-card SERP styling. Sister glw v7.625. tsc clean.
// 8.745 — 🥼 OG image sister sweep — 4 more pages: /order, /careers, /heroes/[cohort], /blog/[slug]. Same Next 16 metadata-cascade quirk as v8.705. All 4 share-previewed imageless. Single `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` per page. Sister glw v7.605. tsc clean.
// 8.725 — 🛡️ PII-leak hardening round 3: 4 sites swept. (1) `app/api/rewards/verify-code/route.ts:224` — `rewards_signed_in_at` UPDATE error echoes the WHERE phone=${phoneE164} clause (customer phone PII). (2) `app/api/track-install/route.ts:102` (auth lookup, Clerk user object echo), (3) `:122` (audit insert payload echo), (4) `:136` (customer update WHERE phone=...). Pre-fix all 4 passed raw `err` to `console.error`. Post-fix: format-only via err.name. Sister of glw v7.585 same wave + v8.575/v8.625 prior PII-leak hardening. tsc clean.
