// 8.575 — 🛡️ PII-leak hardening: format-only error logging on 4 customer-data routes (`app/api/push/subscribe`, `app/api/push/unsubscribe`, `app/api/heroes`, `app/api/profile`). Pre-fix all 4 passed raw `err` into `console.error`, which Vercel logs at full structure. The error objects can echo: push subscription endpoint URLs (per-device stable identifier — Apple/Google/Mozilla push-service URL with token), Clerk user IDs + email + fullName, inbound-payload values (cleanName, phone, SMS/email opt-in, heroes-discount type). Customer PII the dispensary should not be logging in plaintext to non-isolated infrastructure. **Fix:** `const reason = err instanceof Error ? err.name : "unknown"; console.error(\`[source] failed: ${'$'}{reason}\`)` — error class only, no payload. Sister of inv v309.605/v310.205/v310.805 + GW v2.79.10/v2.82.40/v2.82.60/v2.82.85 PHI-leak hardening + glw v7.425 same-wave fix. tsc clean.
