// 26.405 — 📰 Blog Article JSON-LD rigor — SEO audit 2026-05-14 Tier-1 #4 fix (sister glw v35.105). Two field upgrades on `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx`'s `articleSchema`: (a) `dateModified` is now ALWAYS emitted (defaults to `datePublished` when post SSoT lacks an explicit `updatedAt`) — Google uses this as a freshness ranking signal in news/blog SERP categories. Pre-fix only emitted when `updatedAt` was set. Not a fabrication: same-day publication is a real signal, not a backdated edit. (b) `author` flipped from `{ "@type": "Organization", name: STORE.name }` to `{ "@type": "Person", name, url }` — Google's "About this result" panel + Anthropic/Perplexity AI source-citation weighting both prefer Person-bound authors over Org. Per-post override comes from new optional `post.author?: { name, url }` field on `Post` type (`lib/posts.ts`); when absent, defaults to store owner Doug Cundiff at `${STORE.website}/about#owner` — known-true author of record (Doug + staff write every post) pending per-post authorship metadata. (c) `mainEntityOfPage` added — pairs with `@id`/`url` to fully resolve Article ↔ WebPage entity for AI scrapers. (d) `publisher` Organization reference retained separately as Article schema requires both. `apiPostToPost` extended to pass through `updatedAt` + `authorName` + `authorUrl` from the inv CMS so future CMS posts pick this up automatically. typecheck queued.
