// 26.705 — ⚡ Perf audit (PERF_AUDIT_NEAR_PAGES_2026_05_14.md) — `next.config.ts` `images:` block now declares `formats: ["image/avif", "image/webp"]` + `minimumCacheTTL: 60 * 60 * 24 * 30` (30 days). Pre-fix: only `remotePatterns` was set, so Next/Image defaulted to WebP-only output + 4hr edge cache. AVIF compresses ~20% smaller than WebP; combined with the longer TTL this cuts byte-weight + cold-edge re-optimization cost across every `<Image>`-rendered surface (menu, brand-logo cards, hero, blog covers, /near hero bands). AVIF support: Chrome/Edge/Firefox/Safari 16+ — older Safari + IE fall through to WebP fallback automatically via `Accept` header negotiation; final fallback is the original format. Next/Image fingerprints `_next/image` URLs so cache-bust on source change is automatic regardless of TTL — 30 days is safe even for menu thumbnails that update on every CMS edit. Sister glw v35.405 same-push. typecheck queued.
